description:
Sprint 19 surfaced multiple drift modes that current skills don't catch: vp-knowledge's SYNERGY-vp-beads.md has stale-aligned rows for features vp-knowledge retired (PreCompact in v0.28.0); vp-knowledge's reciprocation pass found 3 actively drifting shared patterns (validate-plugin.mjs, check-hooks.mjs, npm-run-all2 — although the latter premise was wrong on inspection). Both directions need ongoing reconciliation.

Provisional name: /sibling-sync (alternative: /sync-tracker, though the existing /vendor-sync precedent argues for verb-shaped names).

Capabilities:
1. read this project's SYNERGY-<sibling>.md alongside the sibling's inverse SYNERGY-<this>.md (path resolved via synergy-registry remote + optional local-path; fall back to ../<sibling>/);
2. diff entries by title and surface gaps in both directions (entries here but not there, or vice versa);
3. flag status conflicts (one side aligned, other drifting);
4. flag stale 'Last verified' dates relative to commit cadence on the artifact paths cited;
5. optionally batch-apply reciprocation under user approval.

Same scaffolding generalizes to UPSTREAM-* files when two siblings share a dependency (e.g., both maintain UPSTREAM-basic-memory.md) — one skill, two file types.

Companion to /vendor-sync (which handles upstream-to-project drift); this skill handles peer-to-peer drift.

Depends on: registry schema extension (separate issue) for path resolution across machines.

Source: ../vp-claude/UPSTREAM-vp-beads.md (entry 5, 2026-05-04).
